The paper deals with a stochastic probing problem with constraints, which is a topic in both algorithms (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of submodular functions is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the approximation algorithms.
